### What’s actually changed

**Legal Calculus (Mayron)** is an open-source, module-based system that packages *procedural literacy, filing templates, and record-building tactics* for pro se users, and it’s publicly available on GitHub [A](https://github.com/cmayron/Legal-Calculus?copilot_analytics_metadata=eyJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tTb3VyY2UiOiJjaXRhdGlvbkxpbmsiLCJldmVudEluZm9fY29udmVyc2F0aW9uSWQiOiJ0U0N6UmtuZzY0U2kyYWZOaktQRkMiLCJldmVudEluZm9fbWVzc2FnZUlkIjoiVnBha2RTb2d1aEFYQ2N6M3pIdzNGIiwiZXZlbnRJbmZvX2NsaWNrRGVzdGluYXRpb24iOiJodHRwczpcL1wvZ2l0aHViLmNvbVwvY21heXJvblwvTGVnYWwtQ2FsY3VsdXMifQ%3D%3D&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1). The project’s public launch materials describe an AI‑assisted “People’s Law School” that helps convert lived experience into admissible, dated evidence and structured filings [B](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/charles-mayron-md-facs-b7043910b_notionai-legalcalculus-accesstojustice-activity-7378903564590632960-3tuD?copilot_analytics_&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1). Commercial legal‑AI platforms offer similar research and drafting assistance at scale, further narrowing the gap for individuals who can use them effectively [C](https://www.cetient.com/pro-se?copilot_analytics_metadata=eyJldmVudEluZm9fY29udmVyc2F0aW9uSWQiOiJ0U0N6UmtuZzY0U2kyYWZOaktQRkMiLCJldmVudEluZm9fbWVzc2FnZUlkIjoiVnBha2RTb2d1aEFYQ2N6M3pIdzNGIiwiZXZlbnRJbmZvX2NsaWNrRGVzdGluYXRpb24iOiJodHRwczpcL1wvd3d3LmNldGllbnQuY29tXC9wcm8tc2UiLCJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tTb3VyY2UiOiJjaXRhdGlvbkxpbmsifQ%3D%3D&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1).

---

### Why this matters (key points)

- **Tooling reduces entry barriers.** Free templates and AI drafting mean *more litigants can produce filings that meet court formatting and procedural expectations*—which historically was a major failure point for pro se parties [A](https://github.com/cmayron/Legal-Calculus?copilot_analytics_metadata=eyJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tTb3VyY2UiOiJjaXRhdGlvbkxpbmsiLCJldmVudEluZm9fY29udmVyc2F0aW9uSWQiOiJ0U0N6UmtuZzY0U2kyYWZOaktQRkMiLCJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tEZXN0aW5hdGlvbiI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC9naXRodWIuY29tXC9jbWF5cm9uXC9MZWdhbC1DYWxjdWx1cyIsImV2ZW50SW5mb19tZXNzYWdlSWQiOiJWcGFrZFNvZ3VoQVhDY3ozekh3M0YifQ%3D%3D&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1) [B](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/charles-mayron-md-facs-b7043910b_notionai-legalcalculus-accesstojustice-activity-7378903564590632960-3tuD?copilot_analytics_&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1).
- **Record-building becomes strategic.** The emphasis on dated, structured evidence shifts leverage: *appeals and procedural posture depend on the record*, and tools that preserve it improve pro se outcomes [B](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/charles-mayron-md-facs-b7043910b_notionai-legalcalculus-accesstojustice-activity-7378903564590632960-3tuD?copilot_analytics_&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1).
- **Asymmetry is reduced but not eliminated.** Big law still controls discovery budgets, expert networks, and courtroom experience; AI narrows *some* gaps (drafting, research) but not all (resources, influence).

---

### Risks, limitations, and trade-offs

- **Accuracy and admissibility:** AI-generated text can contain errors or hallucinations; courts may scrutinize pro se filings more harshly if they appear formulaic or inaccurate [C](https://www.cetient.com/pro-se?copilot_analytics_metadata=eyJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tTb3VyY2UiOiJjaXRhdGlvbkxpbmsiLCJldmVudEluZm9fY2xpY2tEZXN0aW5hdGlvbiI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cuY2V0aWVudC5jb21cL3Byby1zZSIsImV2ZW50SW5mb19jb252ZXJzYXRpb25JZCI6InRTQ3pSa25nNjRTaTJhZk5qS1BGQyIsImV2ZW50SW5mb19tZXNzYWdlSWQiOiJWcGFrZFNvZ3VoQVhDY3ozekh3M0YifQ%3D%3D&citationMarker=9F742443-6C92-4C44-BF58-8F5A7C53B6F1).
- **Ethical and practice limits:** Unauthorized practice of law concerns and jurisdictional nuances remain; pro se users must avoid relying on AI as a substitute for legal advice.
- **Arms race:** Corporations can also adopt advanced AI and bespoke workflows, preserving advantages in complex litigation.

